[2
Date: Mon, 18 Sep 2000 12:35:32 -0400
From: Joseph R Parrish Jr <JoeParrish@compuserve.com>

Possible explanation [for the resurgence of West Nile virus infection in
Israel and the reduced number of fatalities in New York City this year
------------------------------------------------------
The most recent report on the outbreak of West Nile virus infection in
Israel contained the following comment: "The reason for this year's outbreak
is still a mystery. One theory is that the bird migratory period began
earlier than usual. Israel does not have more mosquitoes than normal, said
Yossi Inbar, deputy director general of the Environment Ministry. Mosquitoes
multiply in standing water, and this has been a dry year even by Israeli
standards".
[May I draw your attention to a Columbia University researcher's theory
that dry seasons mean lower bird populations around the mosquito breeding
grounds, and then the mosquitos feed on humans as a secondary source. It
seems to explain the lower incidence this year in New York City and the
higher incidence last year and this may be an explanation for the higher
incidence in Israel now.
--
Joseph R Parrish Jr
<JoeParrish@compuserve.com>
